10/08/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Authorities have started searching Perucac Lake on the Drina River for remains of people killed years ago during the conflicts in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) and Kosovo.
The head of Serbia's committee for missing people, Veljko Odalovic, said on Monday (August 9th) that some human remains have been found.
Requests to search the location came from the Missing Persons Institute of BiH and Pristina's working group for missing people.
(Beta, Radio Free Europe, Tanjug, B92 - 09/08/10)
